  <summary>7/22/1998--Introduced.
Community Forestry and Agriculture Conservation Act of 1998 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to treat a bond issued to acquire renewable resources on land subject to a conservation easement as a tax-exempt (qualified 501(c)(3)) bond if the revenues from such resources' use or sale are used in a manner consistent with the charitable purpose of the issuer although not used as otherwise required.</summary>
